verses.text_plain: The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament sheweth his handywork.
verses.verse_html: 1The heavens declare the glory of God; and the firmament sheweth his handywork.

verses.text_plain: Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night sheweth knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 2Day unto day uttereth speech, and night unto night sheweth knowledge.

verses.text_plain: There is no speech nor language, where their voice is not heard.
verses.verse_html:
3There is no speech nor language, where their voice is not heard. ▼
▼ where…: or, without these their voice is heard: Heb. without their voice heard

footnotes.body_text: ▼ where…: or, without these their voice is heard: Heb. without their voice heard
footnotes.body_html: ▼ where…: or, without these their voice is heard: Heb. without their voice heard

verses.text_plain: Their line is gone out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world. In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun,
verses.verse_html:
4Their line is gone out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world. In them hath he set a tabernacle for the sun, ▼
▼ line: or, rule, or, direction

footnotes.body_html: ▼ line: or, rule, or, direction

verses.text_plain: Which is as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber, and rejoiceth as a strong man to run a race.
verses.verse_html: 5Which is as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber, and rejoiceth as a strong man to run a race.

verses.text_plain: His going forth is from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.
verses.verse_html: 6His going forth is from the end of the heaven, and his circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.

tokens.text: of it: and there is nothing hid

verses.text_plain: The law of the Lord is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the Lord is sure, making wise the simple.
verses.verse_html:
7The law of the Lord is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the Lord is sure, making wise the simple. ▼
▼ law: or, doctrine
 , ▼
▼ converting: or, restoring

verses.text_plain: The statutes of the Lord are right, rejoicing the heart: the commandment of the Lord is pure, enlightening the eyes.
verses.verse_html: 8The statutes of the Lord are right, rejoicing the heart: the commandment of the Lord is pure, enlightening the eyes.

verses.text_plain: The fear of the Lord is clean, enduring for ever: the judgments of the Lord are true and righteous altogether.
verses.verse_html:
9The fear of the Lord is clean, enduring for ever: the judgments of the Lord are true and righteous altogether. ▼
▼ true: Heb. truth

verses.text_plain: More to be desired are they than gold, yea, than much fine gold: sweeter also than honey and the honeycomb.
verses.verse_html:
10More to be desired are they than gold, yea, than much fine gold: sweeter also than honey and the honeycomb. ▼
▼ the honeycomb: Heb. the dropping of honeycombs

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the honeycomb: Heb. the dropping of honeycombs
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the honeycomb: Heb. the dropping of honeycombs

verses.text_plain: Moreover by them is thy servant warned: and in keeping of them there is great reward.
verses.verse_html: 11Moreover by them is thy servant warned: and in keeping of them there is great reward.

tokens.text: Moreover by them is thy servant

verses.text_plain: Who can understand his errors? cleanse thou me from secret faults.
verses.verse_html: 12Who can understand his errors? cleanse thou me from secret faults.

verses.text_plain: Keep back thy servant also from presumptuous sins; let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent from the great transgression.
verses.verse_html:
13Keep back thy servant also from presumptuous sins; let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent from the great transgression. ▼
▼ the great: or, much

tokens.text: over me: then shall I be upright

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the great: or, much

verses.text_plain: Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in thy sight, O Lord, my strength, and my redeemer.
verses.verse_html:
14Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in thy sight, O Lord, my strength, and my redeemer. ▼
▼ strength: Heb. rock
